.so ../bk-macros
.TH "bk makepatch" 1 20%E% "\*(BC" "\*(UM"
.SH NAME
bk makepatch \- creates \*(BK patches
.SH SYNOPSIS
.Bc bk makepatch [\-vd] [
.OPTreq \-c range
.Bc ] [
.OPTreq \-e range
.Bc ] [
.OPTreq \-r range
.Bc ] [-
.B ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.LP
The makepatch command is a low level command used to generate \*(BK patches.
.SH OPTIONS
.if t .TP .7i
.if n .TP 1i
.B \-c
Like \-r, except generate only ChangeSet diffs.  Used for logging only.
.tp
.B \-d
Add a header with the unified diffs to the top of the \*(BK patch.
.tp
.OPTreq \-e range
Like \-r, except generate only metadata diffs.  Used for logging only.
.tp
.OPTreq \-r range
Generate a \*(BK patch of the changes in
.ARG range .
.tp
.B \-v
Be more verbose for each instance.
.SH NOTES
The supported interface for creating \*(BK patches is bk send.  And 
bk export -tpatch should be used to create GNU patches.
.SH SEE ALSO
.SA cset 1
.SA export 1
.SA gnupatch 1
.SA rset 1
.SH CATEGORY
.B Repository
